The paper deals with algorithmic fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the pitfalls of naive composition and gives general constructions for fair composition, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the social implications of algorithmic fairness, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
